CONJUNCTIONS (CONNECTORS, LINKING WORDS)									     prepared by Uğur ARSLAN, @arslanuguur
      - Coordinating Conjunctions		düzenleyen bağlaçlar		independent(bağımsız cümle) + dependent (bağımlı cümle)
            - for, and, nor, but, or, yet, so
      - Correlative Conjunctions		bağıntılı bağlaçlar (ikili bağlaçlar)
            -- too, also, so, also
      - Subordinating Conjunctions		bağımlı bağlaçlar		dependent/independent + independent


CONJUNCTIONS
# COORDINATING CONJUNCTIONS - FANBOYS
	--> FOR
		Shows a reason or purpose. 
		Using 'for' in this way can often be seen as quite formal, 
		and so is usually replaced with the word 'because', 'since', or 'as'.
      			The money I earned is gone, for I have spent it all.

	--> AND
		Connects two similar ideas.
      			I have to be at work, and the doctor's.
            			I have to be at work
            			I have to be at the doctor's.
      			I'm going to learn how to play the guitar and piano.
           			I'm going to learn how to play the guitar.
            			I'm going to learn how to play the piano.
            
	--> NOR
		Now can be interchanged with 'neither' and compares a negative, contrasting Idea. 
		Essentially, it is the opposite of 'and'.
      			I cannot go to work, nor the doctor's.
      			I'm not going to learn to play the guitar, nor the piano.

	--> BUT
		Compares to contrasting ideas or highlights an exception.
      			I can go to the pool, but I won't swim.
            		Idea:             I can go to the pool
            		Contrasting idea: I won’t swim.

		It can also be used in a way that says, ‘not this, but that’.
      			The noise wasn’t coming from a computer, but rather a phone.
       			I know you have had a bad day but you don't have to take it out on me 

	--> OR
		Or highlights two choices.
      			You can choose a blue jumper or a pink jumper.
      			They were either angry or sad.
      			Do you want vanilla or chocolate cake?

	--> YET
		Yet is used in a way to show an exception or a contrast to an idea.
   			There are five cars, yet none of them are working.
    			I drank a full bottle of water, yet I still felt thirsty.

	--> SO
		So is used to show a reaction or consequence.
    			I ate a lot of cookies, so there are none left.
			I was feeling anxious, so I went home.


- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - 
---> TOO, ALSO, SO, AS WELL, EITHER (TÜRKÇEDEKİ DAHİ (DE, DA ANLAMINDA))
	I work here too			ben de çalışıyorum
	I also work here		ben de çalışıyorum
	I work here as well		burada da çalışıyorum
	as well as I work here		Burada çalışıyorum da
	so do I				ben de burda çalışıyorum
	me either / me too		ben de burda çalışıyorum
	it wont be one of them either	ikisinden biri de olmayacak
	
	--> ALSO
		- getting no message, is also a message
		- He was also dressed for the exclusive party
		- Both William and Catherine would also attend
		- She also lost her sense of smell and taste
		- It’s very humid. Also, you can easily get sunburnt
		- I’ll phone you next week and we can discuss it then. Also, we need to decide who will be going to Singapore
		
		
	--> SO
		- I am a student 		--> "So I am," replied she.
		- my wife likes shopping 	--> "So is Martha," he answered with a laugh.
		- you also talked with her? 	-->  "So did I," he interrupted. 
		- he has seen her on the street --> So have I
		- she had loved you 		--> So had I, but it's not possible any more 
		- I didn't realize you were so sensitive about it.***
		- I told you so.***
		
	--> TOO 
		- 15 + 15 is thirty and 16 + 16 is thirty too
                - if you’re going to the mall, can I come too?
		- I love you too, sweetie. = me too
		- "Ah, you've come here too, young man!" he said
		- Gill’s having chicken. I’ll probably have chicken too
		- She looks really tired and she must be really hungry too
		
	--> EITHER
		- Bill’s not here. I don’t think Dave is either, is he?
		- I can't sleep either		
		- no, no, don't answer that either
		- what if they don't talk, either?
		- I don't know why either	- I don't know anything about either
		- you don't trust me, either
		- it wasn't either of your faults
		- I am not going 		- nor am I
		- he can't drive, and neither can she
		
	--> AS WELL
		- A: I’ll have steak please
    		  B: Yes
    		  A: And I’ll have the mixed vegetables as well
		- if he had lied to her, he might have cheated as well
		- I think you felt something as well
		- She must have suspected as well
		- There was little sound from the kitchen as well
		- He obviously missed Julia as well
		- She can decide for herself as well
		
		--> AS WELL AS - yanı sıra
		- He could be tender and thoughtful, as well as charming
		- I know you as well as I know anyone else
		- This wasn't going as well as she had planned
		- In fact, they were a police force as well as an army
		



---> CORRELATIVE CONJUNCTIONS (Paired Conjuntions)
	--> BOTH ... AND ...			--> hem ... hem de ...
		- we'll have both the cheesecake and the chocolate cake
		- he can both sing and play the violin
		- I am finished with both my English essay and my history essay

	--> EITHER ... OR ...			--> ya ... ya da ...
		- a man either cheats or he doesn't.
		- either come in, or go think somewhere else
		- she either doesn't understand or is pretending
		- you can have either tea or coffee 
		
	--> NEITHER ... NOR ...			--> ne ... ne de ...
		- by the way, neither Alex nor I drink
		- he heard neither the clock nor the birds
		- they knew neither her name nor anything about her
		- he will neither visit the museum nor attend the conference
		- neither will he visit the museum nor will he attend the conference
	
	--> NOT ONLY ... BUT ALSO / AS WELL	--> sadece ... değil, aynı zamanda ...
      		- not only John but also George is from London
		- not only did he invite his cousins but also his close friends 
		- Not only am I finished studying for English, but I’m also finished writing my history essay.

      	--> SO ... AS				--> kadar ... çok
      		- he can’t run so fast as George
	
	--> SO ... THAT				--> öyle ... ki
		- he spoke so quickly that nobody understood what he said
	
	--> AS ... AS				--> kadar
		- the flat that we will buy must be as cheap as possible
		- he can’t run as fast as George
		- Jane is as rich as Peter
	
	--> SUCH ... THAT			--> öyle ... ki
		- he is such a good player that many teams are eager to transfer him
	
	--> THE MORE ... THE MORE		--> ne kadar ... o kadar ...
		- the more you work, the more you earn
		- the longer they play, the more they lose- ne kadar uzun oynarlarsa o kadar kaybederler
		- the more a man has in himself, the less he will want from other people
			bir insan kendi içinde ne kadar çok şeye sahipse, diğer insanlardan o kadar az şey isteyecektir 
	
	--> NO SOONER ... THAN 			--> demeye kalmadan, yapar yapmaz
		- he had no sooner opened his eyes than the phone rang
		- no sooner had he opened his eyes than the phone rang
	
	--> WHETHER ... OR			--> ya da sevmesin	
		- he will have to cooperate with us, whether he likes us or not
		- Idk whether I will come or not
	
	--> RATHER ... THAN
		- i would rather stay at home than go out tonight
	
	--> HARDLY ... WHEN			--> zar zor	
		- he had hardly found a job when he got ill
		- hardly had he found a job when he got ill
	
	--> SCARCELY ... WHEN			--> ucu ucuna, ancak
		- he had scarcely gone to bed when the phone rang
		- scarcely had he gone to bed when the phone rang







---> SUBORDINATING CONJUNCTIONS
--> Time
		after			-den sonra
						after several rings, it went to the message
						after a few moments, he glanced up at her
		before			-den önce
						I worked with him for two years before I discovered who he really was
						it took some time before I could plan it to suit me	bana uyacak şekilde planlayabilmem biraz zaman aldı 
		when			-dığı zaman
						he had climbed many a tree when he was a boy
						when she woke again, the room was dark
		while			iken, sırada
						I don't want you to drive while you're so tired
						next week today, I will be lying on the beach while you are working 
		as			iken, sırada
						as they looked down the street they saw a horseman coming
							sokağın aşağısına baktıklarında bir atlının geldiğini gördüler
						his gaze drifted away as he considered the idea			bu fikri düşünürken bakışları başka yöne kaydı
		just as			tıpkı, gibi
						just as I walked into the room, I noticed a big spider on my bed
		
		by the time		zamana kadar
						it will be almost midnight by the time we arrive home
						most of the guests were already there by the time we arrived at the party
		since			-den beri
						she has made considerable progress since she started attending school more regularly
						he has been looking for a job since he graduated, but hasn't found one yet
						it is almost a year since she has been married
						since when did we start following the rules?			ne zamandan beri kurallara uyduk?
		until / till		-a kadar
						I will stay up until midnight tomorrow
						I wont say much till it’s time to go to bed
						
		not until		-den önce değil, -meden önce, kadar olmaz, kadar değil
						no, not until you tell me how it went			hayır, nasıl gittiğini anlatana kadar olmaz
		eventually 		er ya da geç, nihayetinde
						everything eventually gets easier with practice		uygulama ile her şey sonunda daha kolay olur
						such secrets are always eventually revealed		bu tür sırlar her zaman sonunda ortaya çıkar
		whenever		ne zaman olursa
		every time (that)	ne zaman .. olsa
						Every time we meet a problem, it always seems to be related to housing
						Naturally i will come to you for advice whenever i feel in need of some
		the first time (that)	ilk kez
		the last time (that)	son kez
		the next time (that)	bir dahaki sefere
		now that		mademki, artık, -dığından
						they're popping up everywhere now that schools have gotten rid of all the bullies
						her yerde bittikleri için okullar artık bütün kabadayılardan kurtuldu
		meanwhile		o esnada
						he does, meanwhile, have motive for resigning his job
						bu arada, işinden istifa etmek için gerekçesi var
		in the meantime		bu arada
						they said I could get started in the meantime
						bu sırada, benim başlayabileceğimi söylediler
		in the past		geçmişte
		currently		şu anda
						applying for an ordinary German passport currently costs USD 50
						şu anda sıradan bir Alman pasaportu için başvuru maliyeti 50 ABD dolarıdır.
		presently		şu anda
						one is presently used as an office/study		şu anda bir çalışma alanı/ofis olarak kullanılmaktadır
		as soon as		yapar yapmaz
						I am going to get out and have a drink as soon as I have finished with the work
						I will call you as soon as I receive your mail
						I recognized Julia as soon as I saw her even though it had been more than a year since I had last seen her
						Some students rush out of the classroom as soon as the class ends
		immediately after	-dan hemen sonrası
						She will call us immediately after she arrives in Antalya, so stop worrying		
		the moment		-dığı an
						She will leave the moment she has sent this message	
		once			yapar yapmaz
						Once the Soviet Union collapsed, Russia Federation was founded in 1991
						If I were you, I wouldn't start smoking at all, because once you start, it is very difficult to give up
						Once I start working for this company, all my financial problems will be over
						Once you have read a book by this author, you will want to read more
					
					1. 'as soon as' ile aynı anlamda 'olur olmaz' anlamında kullanılabilir. Bu yönüyle 'after' anlamında da diyebiliriz
						We can go out once I finish my work		İşimi bitirir bitirmez dışarı çıkabiliriz
					
					2. Cümlede 'bir kez' anlamında kullanılabilir
						Once I make up my mind, nothing can stop me.	Bir kez karar verdim mi, beni hiçbir şey durduramaz
						
					3. Cümlede 'bir zamanlar' anlamında kullanılabilir
						I once lived in İstanbul			Bir zamanlar İstanbul'da yaşadım.
						
						
		as long as / so long as	-dığı sürece
						As long as it is raining, i think i will stay at home
						You can stay with us as long as you want
		at last			sonunda		(-)
		finally			en sonunda 	(+)
		hence			bundan dolayı
		hardly/barely/scarcely  ... when
		no sooner ... than	... dan önce olamaz
		during			sırasında, esnasında	
						during the lecture, all the students took notes

		NOTE:
			at last / finally = lastly / in the end / at the end / by the end
			- After a two-hour delay, Tom's plane has landed at last.
			- When he arrived at last, I was so angry that I refused to talk to him.
			- Our economy must increase productivity, reduce unemployment and finally develop competition
			- We must buy flour, chocolate, butter, eggs and lastly some baking powder to make a cake for her birthday
			- Each of us suggested a different plan for our holiday, but in the end we went to the South of France as usual
			- Put a full stop at the end of your sentence
			- Don't worry! She'll be here by the end of the morning.

			at last = sonunda
			at least = en azından

--> Emphasis
		indeed			aslında, doğrusu
		 				His only fault indeed seems Modesty	
							Tek hatası, doğrusu, alçak gönüllülüğü gibi görünüyor. 
		obviously		açıkçası
						Well, obviously, Amazon is able to collect this data as they make sales
							Eh, belli ki Amazon bu verileri satış yaparken toplayabiliyor
		particularly		özellikle de
						 Winter months pose particularly difficult conditions for riders
							Kış ayları özellikle sürücüler için oldukça zor zamanları beraberinde getiriyor
		in particular		özellikle, bilhassa
						 Because it seems like she is interested in you in particular
							Çünkü anlaşılan bu kız seninle özel olarak ilgileniyor
		especially		özellikle
						Information is always changing, especially in healthcare
		clearly			açıkça
						Three ongoing cases clearly demonstrate these concerns.
							Halen devam eden üç dava bu kaygıları açıkça göstermektedir 
		more importantly	daha da önemlisi
						 More importantly, I want you to feel comfortable being yourself
							Daha da önemlisi, kendin olma konusunda rahat olmanı istiyorum. 
		absolutely		kesinlikle
						he absolutely must see her, however painful it may be for him
		definitely		kesinlikle, mutlaka
						 it definitely needs time to improve.
							daha iyi gelişmeler için mutlaka zamana ihtiyaç var
						 This will definitely influence your decision
							Bu da sizin kararınızı mutlaka etkisi altına alacaktır
		without a doubt		şüphesiz, kuşkusuz, hiç şüphe etmeden 
						Hybrids and electric vehicles are without a doubt the future of cleaner motoring.
							Hibrit ve elektrikli araçlar kuşkusuz daha temiz motor sisteminin geleceğidir 
		undoubtedly		şüphesiz
						 You'll undoubtedly perish in this ridiculous scheme.
							Hiç şüphesiz, saçma bir planın içinde, yok olup gideceksiniz. 
		never			asla
						 Someone recently told me never to say never.
							Yakınlarda birisi bana asla, asla dememem gerektiğini öğretti 
		it should be noted	belirtilmelidir ki
						However, it should be noted, and some features of this device that must be discussed.
							Bununla birlikte, bu cihazın ve tartışılması gereken bazı özelliklerinin de belirtilmesi gerekir. 
		as a matter of fact	aslına bakarsan
						 And as a matter of fact I keep asking myself the same question.
							Ve aslına bakarsanız, ben de bu soruyu kendime sık sık soruyorum. 


--> Addition
		so that			böylece, öyle ki
						 I took a job up here, so that we could meet.
							Burada bir iş aldım, böylece görüşebiliriz
		even so			olsa bile, yine de, buna rağmen
						 But even so, considering the conditions
							Ama öyle olsa bile, içinde bulunduğumuz durumu göz önüne alırsak
		in spite of		karşın, e rağmen
						 But in spite of our efforts, the doctor started to feel lonely.
							Ancak tüm çabamıza rağmen doktor kendini yalnız hissetmeye başladı. 
		regardless of		gözetilmeksizin, bakılmaksızın
						show respect for everyone who works for living, regardless of how trivial their job
							işleri ne kadar önemsiz olursa olsun, yaşamak için çalışan herkese saygı göster
		due to			nedeniyle, dolayısıyla, yüzünden
						 The Peace Process has unfortunately stalled due to unexpected, unforeseen circumstances.
							Ne yazık ki barış süreci umulmadık, öngörülemeyen şartlardan ötürü durmuş haldedir. 
		by means of		aracılığıyla, vasıtasıyla
						 Each customer pays for the service by means of a subscription
							Her müşteri, bir abonelik aracılığıyla hizmet için ödeme yapar
						 We express our thoughts by means of languages.
							Biz düşüncelerimizi diller vasıtasıyla ifade ederiz. 
		nonetheless		her şeye rağmen, yine de, bununla birlikte
						 Nothing particularly remarkable, but useful nonetheless.
							Özellikle dikkat çekici bir şey değil, ama yine de işe yarar. 
		further			daha ötesi, daha fazlası
						For further details, please see 4.
							Daha fazla bilgi için, lütfen EK 4'e bakın.
						Some German companies have already announced further investment.
							Alman şirketleri de nihayet daha fazla yatırım malı almaya başladılar. 
		furthermore		üstelik, ayrıca
						 And furthermore, use all means to get this criminal to talk.
							Üstelik bu suçluyu konuşturmak için her türlü yolu kullanın.
						 That group, furthermore, disproportionately represents the highest unemployment benefit amounts.
							Bu grup aynı zamanda orantısız şekilde en yüksek işsizlik ödenekleri miktarını temsil etmektedir. 
		also			ayrıca
						Also, Ankara contacted us regarding water for its residents in Çankaya
							Ayrıca Ankara, Çankaya'da yaşayanlar için su konusunda bizimle iletişime geçti
		too			hem de
						She said we have to see it, too - Bizim de görmemiz gerektiğini söyledi
						Maybe he was going to show her he could be a nice guy too
						You might want to watch out for him too - Sen de ona göz kulak olmak isteyebilirsin.
		besides			dışında, yanı sıra
						She knows four hundred phrases besides numerous words
						Where else did you go besides the barber shop?
		finally			en sonunda
						Finally she put the knife down and started putting the sliced meat in a plastic container
							Sonunda bıçağı indirdi ve dilimlenmiş eti plastik bir kaba koymaya başladı
		last			en son
						It seems like years since I saw you last
						she might not find the way if she didn't know where they'd been last
							en son nerede olduklarını bilmeseydi yolu bulamayabilirdi
		apart from		dışında
						But you're here now, and apart from the obvious, you look good
							Ama buradasın ve dış görünüşün dışında iyi görünüyorsun
						It had become clear that, apart from their scientific aspects, these voyages of discovery were highly profitable
							 Bilimsel yönlerinin yanı sıra, bu keşif yolculuklarının oldukça karlı olduğu ortaya çıkmıştı
						Mary has only ever had one other boyfriend, apart from Tom.
						 	Mary'nin Tom dışında sadece bir erkek arkadaşı oldu
		along with		ile birlikte
						For depression along with conventional antidepressants, it must be consumed fish oil 9.6 grams/day.
		additionally		bunlara ek olarak, aynı zamanda
						Samsung has additionally worked hard to reduce noise in computers, too
							Samsung aynı zamanda bilgisiyarlarda gürültüyü azaltmak için de çok çalıştı 
		in addition to this	buna ek olarak, bunun yanı sıra
						in addition to this the building work continues.
							bunun yanı sıra inşaat işi de devam ediyor. 
		then			ondan sonra
						Start at low speeds, then accelerate, then slow down again
							Düşük hızda başla, ondan sonra hızlan, ondan sonra tekrar yavaşla
		moreover		dahası, üstelik
						 The house looked good; moreover, the price was right.
							Ev iyi görünüyordu, üstelik fiyat en uygundu. 
		as well as (that)	yanı sıra
						 This lifestyle modification helps treat as well as prevent various diseases.
							Bu yaşam tarzı değişikliği çeşitli hastalıkları önlemenin yanı sıra tedaviye de yardımcı olur. 
		what’s more		dahası
						and what's more, I know who did it
						my sister can ride a motorcycle, and what's more, a bicycle
							Kız kardeşim bir motosiklet sürebilir, ve dahası bir bisikleti de. 
		not only ... but also	sadece ... değil, aynı zamanda


--> Opinion
		in my opinion		benim görüşüme göre
						the committee adopted too many amendments, in my opinion
		as far as i’m concerned	ilgilendiğim kadarıyla
						at least, as far as I can see, he'll be fine
						there was no other way to look at it as far as she was concerned	
		to my mind		bana göre
						because to my mind, viewing the subject as a whole, would be intelligible
		i think			sanırım, bence
						I think, the birth rate will go down in my country in the next few years
		it seems to me that	bana öyle geliyor ki
						it seems to me that the situation really is very confused
		

--> Summary
		in short		kısacası
		in the word		tek kelimeyle
		anyway			her neyse
		in brief		kısaca
		briefly			kısaca
		it seems		anlaşılan
		clearly			açıkça
		in sum			toplamda
		to sum up		sonuç olarak
		in summary		özetle
		to summarize		özetlemek
		after all		herşeye rağmen, nihayet
		in general		genel olarak
		in conclusion		sonuç olarak
		altogether		tamamen
		to conclude		sonuçlandırmak 


--> Order
		firstly			ilk olarak
		secondly		ikinci olarak 
		thirdly			üçüncü olarak
		finally			en sonunda, sonuçta
		at this time		şu anda
		following		takip edilen, aşağıdaki
		previously		önceki
		before			önceden
		subsequently		sonradan
		above all		her şeyden önce
		last but not least	sonuncu ama bir o kadar önemli
		first and foremost	ilk ve en önemli
						firstly and foremost, they can give up at any point
							ilk ve en önemlisi, istedikleri anda vazgeçebilirler


--> Result (Consequence)
