--> Contrast (Concession and Opposition)
		but			ama, fakat			I wanted to go but I didn't have any money
		yet			ama, fakat, henüz		The tongue is not made of steel, yet, it cuts
		but ... anyway		ama ... neyse
		but ... still		ama ... halen, yine de
		yet ... still		ama ... halen
		still			hala, halen			I have still got tons to do
									I don't think we can stay longer but still, we will have fun		

		whereas			halbuki, oysa
		while			iken
		on the one hand		bir taraftan
		on the other hand	diğer taraftan
		as opposed to		aksine
		on the contrary		tam tersine, tam aksine		It wasn't a good thing; on the contrary it was a huge mistake
									It doesn't seem ugly to me; on the contrary, I think it's rather beautiful
		in contrast		tam tersine/aksine		It was cold yesterday, but in contrast, it's very hot today
									In contrast with last year's profits, the company is not doing very well
		contrary to		aksine				contrary to what most people believe, spinach is not very rich in iron
		otherwise		aksi halde
		instead of		onun yerine
		even if			olsa bile			be brave. even if you are not, pretend to be. no one can tell the difference
		even so			öyle olsa bile			It was raining, but even so we had to go out
									There are a lot of spelling mistakes; even so, it's quite a good essay
									I had a terrible headache, but even so I went to the concert
		no matter		ne yaparsa yapsın
		whatever		her ne ise
		wherever		her neresi ise
		whenever		he ne zamansa
		but for			ama için
		however + adj/ adv	ancak + adj/ adv 		the weather was quite cold. however, he still went jogging
									This is a cheap and simple process, however, there are dangers
									I feel a bit tired, however, I can hold on
		nevertheless		yine de				There are serious problems in our country. Nevertheless, we feel this is a good time to return
		nonetheless		herşeye rağmen, yine de (resmi) The book is too long but, nonetheless, informative and entertaining

		apart from		dışında
		admittedly		kuşkusuz
		all the same		farketmez, yine de
		up to a point		bu noktaya kadar

		although		olmasına rağmen			Although he promised to come, I still didn’t think he would
		though			rağmen
		even though		buna rağmen
		much as			buna rağmen			
		despite the fact that	bu gerçeğe rağmen
		in spite of the fact that - ... e rağmen, ... se bile
	
		although + clause 	--> ... e rağmen	he can’t speak English although he has been attending a course for two years
		though + clause 	--> ... e rağmen	though I knew the answer, I didn’t tell it
		even though + clause	--> ... e rağmen	even though there weren’t enough funds, the government decided to make new investments
		despite + noun 		--> ... e rağmen	he went out despite the rain
								he couldn’t succeed despite his effort
								despite being disabled, she has made great achievements
		in spite of + noun	--> ... e rağmen	in spite of the rain, they had the party outside
								he decided to go in spite of my objection

		neither .. nor	ne o ne de o			You neither know how to sing nor how to dance
								I neither speak German nor understand it
								Neither Brian nor his wife mentioned anything about moving house
			


--> Condition
		CÜMLE ALANLAR
		on condition that	şartıyla
		provided that		şartıyla
		providing that		sağlanması şartıyla, koşuluyla
		so long as		sürece
		as long as		sürece
						This should work, as long as they haven't changed the password.
							Şifreyi değiştirmedikleri müddetçe, bu işe yarayacaktır.
						As long as it takes - ne kadar gerekirse
						Everything will be fine as long as we stay outside the bubble.
							Balondan uzak durduğumuz sürece her şey yolunda gidecektir.
		unless			olmazsa, olmadıkça, tabi		 (kendisi olumsuz olduğu için devamındaki cümle olumsuz olmaz)
						Not unless there was something else			Tabi başka bir şey varsa o ayrı
						That's impossible, unless they're still in town		Bu imkansız, tabii hala kasabada değillerse
						Women can't drive you unless you give them your keys 
		if			eğer
						We got locked out of our apartment. would you mind if we waited in here until the locksmith comes?
						Dairemizin dışında kaldık. çilingir gelene kadar burada beklememizin bir sakıncası var mı? 
		only if			yalnızca
		assuming that		varsayarsak
		in that case		bu durumda
		in case (that)		durumunda, halinde
						in case he comes back, what are we supposed to do?
						And I just needed you to know that in case.. 	Bu durumda şunu bilmem gerekiyor..
		even if			olsa bile
		in the event (that)	durumunda
		supposing		varsayalım
		if so			eğer öyleyse
		whether or not		öyle ya da böyle
		in order to		amacıyla, -mek için, diye
						People devised shelters in order to protect themselves.
							İnsanlar kendilerini korumak için sığınaklar tasarladı.
		so that			böylece
		otherwise		aksi halde
		or (else)		veya (başka) 
	
	
	
	

--> Reason (Purpose / Cause and Effect)
		CÜMLE ALANLAR
		since, because, for, as long as, so long as, now that, in as much as   -- dığı için, çünkü

		İSİM ALANLAR
		because of, due to, owing to (the fact that), on account of, in view of, thanks to, by reason of
		
		
		because, since, as
			because our transport company is rather small, we sometimes manage to offer a discount on the sea freight
			since all the buses were crowded, i took a taxi yesterday
		
		on the grounds that – mesi sebebiyle/gerekçesiyle

		now that – artık … -dığına göre
			Now that everybody is here, we can start the conference
			Now that the work is finished, i am going to rest a few hours
	
		seeing that – madem ki
			seeing that you have already made your decision, there isn't much I can do
				madem çoktan kararını verdin, yapabileceğim pek bir şey yok
		
		inas much as – çünkü
			inas much as you couldnt make a decision, you should stop complaining about it
	
		in that – çünkü

		so that, in order (to) (that), to, so as to, what this in mind, in fact, for fear that

		as long as, so long as, inasmuch as, lest, such ... that, so ... that
			as long as you want to, you can stay in this city
			so long as you eat a well-branced diet you will be all right
	
		therefore, consequently, so
			... mek için			--> in order to, so as to, to + Ving
			... mek için, … sın diye 	--> in order that, so that + clause

		So, therefore, as a result, consequently, hence, that's why – bu yüzden, sonuç olarak
			it was rather cold, so we had to stay at home
			it hasnt rained for three months. Therefore, the farmers are having hard times
			they left home late. They, therefore, misssed the bus (therefore)
			there was a lot of noise in the neighborhood. Consequently, he had to move to another place
		


